When It's All Said And Done... Take Time
When It's All Said And Done... Take Time

“MONTERO (Call Me By Your Name)” may be the most talked-about song on the planet right now, but for Lil Nas X, the powerful, provocative track is about so much more than a viral moment. “It’s brought a new confidence out of me,” the singer and rapper tells Apple Music. “To be able to say, ‘You know what? I want to do this.’ And I don’t give a fuck who’s upset about it. I feel like the moment I put this snippet out of this song, I just started to see a shift in myself gradually.” “MONTERO” (a nod to Lil Nas X's real name, Montero Lamar Hill) is a dizzying, unapologetic mash-up of flamenco, hip-hop, pop and trap, designed to celebrate the artist’s queer identity—and usher in a new era of liberation. “If I’m ever doing something to grab attention, there’s always a fight or meaning behind it,” adds the rapper. “There’s always new doors opened for artists in the future to do that thing and it won’t be a big deal anymore... [This song] was liberating.” Elsewhere, hear the biggest new hits from Justin Bieber, Joel Corry, RAYE and David Guetta, and KSI.
